NAME
    Sah::SchemaBundle::Identifier - Sah schemas related to identifiers

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.002 of Sah::SchemaBundle::Identifier
    (from Perl distribution Sah-SchemaBundle-Identifier), released on
    2025-11-11.

SAH SCHEMAS
    The following schemas are included in this distribution:

    *   identifier

        A string that starts with [A-Za-z_] followed by zero of more
        [A-Za-z0-9_].

        Identifier is an often-used definition for relatively safe names you
        can put into file name, tack onto variable name, and so on.

    *   identifier127

        Identifier with a maximum length of 127 characters.

        Just like "identifier", but limited to 127 characters.

    *   identifier15

        Identifier with a maximum length of 15 characters.

        Just like "identifier", but limited to 15 characters.

    *   identifier255

        Identifier with a maximum length of 255 characters.

        Just like "identifier", but limited to 255 characters. Can be used,
        e.g. for file names in Unix filesystem.

    *   identifier31

        Identifier with a maximum length of 31 characters.

        Just like "identifier", but limited to 31 characters.

    *   identifier63

        Identifier with a maximum length of 63 characters.

        Just like "identifier", but limited to 63 characters.

    *   identifier::lc

        A string that starts with [a-z_] followed by zero of more [a-z0-9_].

        Just like "identifier", but must contain lowercase [a-z] only.

    *   identifier::lc127

        Lowercase Identifier with a maximum length of 127 characters.

        Just like "identifier::lc", but limited to 127 characters.

    *   identifier::lc15

        Lowercase Identifier with a maximum length of 15 characters.

        Just like "identifier::lc", but limited to 15 characters.

    *   identifier::lc255

        Lowercase Identifier with a maximum length of 255 characters.

        Just like "identifier::lc", but limited to 255 characters.

    *   identifier::lc31

        Lowercase Identifier with a maximum length of 31 characters.

        Just like "identifier::lc", but limited to 31 characters.

    *   identifier::lc63

        Lowercase Identifier with a maximum length of 63 characters.

        Just like "identifier::lc", but limited to 63 characters.

    *   identifier::no_u

        A string that starts with [a-z] followed by zero of more [a-z0-9].

        This is a version of "identifier" that does not allow underscores,
        everywhere.

    *   identifier::no_u_delim

        A string that starts with [a-z] followed by zero of more [a-z0-9_]
        and ends with [a-z0-9].

        This is a version of "identifier" that does not allow underscore
        delimiters. Underscore is still allowed in the middle.

    *   identifier::uc

        A string that starts with [A-Z_] followed by zero of more [A-Z0-9_].

        Just like "identifier", but must contain uppercase [A-Z] only.

    *   identifier::uc127

        Uppercase Identifier with a maximum length of 127 characters.

        Just like "identifier::uc", but limited to 127 characters.

    *   identifier::uc15

        Uppercase Identifier with a maximum length of 15 characters.

        Just like "identifier::uc", but limited to 15 characters.

    *   identifier::uc255

        Uppercase Identifier with a maximum length of 255 characters.

        Just like "identifier::uc", but limited to 255 characters.

    *   identifier::uc31

        Uppercase Identifier with a maximum length of 31 characters.

        Just like "identifier::uc", but limited to 63 characters.

    *   identifier::uc63

        Uppercase Identifier with a maximum length of 63 characters.

        Just like "identifier::uc", but limited to 63 characters.

DESCRIPTION
    "Identifiers" are often used as safe strings for names.

